issue.title: Intro
issue.body: During the intro Alexa should include saying that she can play the scale for you, otherwise users don't know that she has to ability to show you the scale.

issue.title: add note guessing game
issue.body: Create a fun note guessing game where a note gets played, then the student guesses what letter is on the scale (A-G).  If they guess correctly, let them go again and create a streak.

issue.title: Titles
issue.body: Not all of the songs include a title in their video. Also, Silent Night is the only song that includes a sub-title.

issue.title: Star Spangled Banner
issue.body: The notes do not show up for the majority of the song so it ends up being a blank picture of a piano for the majority of the time.

issue.title: White rings
issue.body: There are no white rings around the orange circles when playing the scale video.

issue.title: Give warning before playing a song
issue.body: Give more time and warning before the song starts so you have time to position your hands. You could include a countdown before the song starts that is displayed on the screen, or you could have Alexa say something like "Ready? Begin!".

issue.title: Notes should play slower
issue.body: When the Piano Teacher skill is teaching you a song, the notes and music tend to go by very fast. This makes it hard to learn a song. There should be more time between notes to solve this problem.

issue.title: Add black notes to the scale
issue.body: On the app it is able to play the scale. However it only shows the white notes on the scale and not the black ones. Some songs include the black notes so it would be helpful if you included the black notes when Alexa plays the scale for you.

issue.title: Have Alexa ask if you want to play again
issue.body: At the end of a song Alexa goes back to the list of other songs to chose from. Instead, Alexa should ask you if you would like to replay the song.
